genresAdvancedInfo.name: cantaditas
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Cantaditas is a type of electronic dance music that originated in Spain in the 1990s. It's characterized by its use of high-pitched, fast-paced vocals, driving beats, and uplifting melodies. Cantaditas often features remixes of popular songs from the 80s and 90s, and has a devoted fan base in Spain and other parts of Europe. It's known for its energetic, party-ready sound and its ability to get people on the dance floor.
